    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with high-ceiling opportunities, anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.02) and **Junior Caminero** (76.66). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is our premier play, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Tobias Myers and a significant boost from a dynamic platoon advantage. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** leverages a favorable wind forecast at his venue to bolster his raw power profile against Mitch Keller. **Trea Turner** remains an essential start (69.15) for his elite category-defying speed, providing a high floor regardless of the matchup against Grant Holmes, while **Yordan Alvarez** (67.90) and **Kyle Schwarber** (66.04) are prioritized for their elite xwOBA metrics, ensuring production even in matchups that aren't perfectly aligned with their handedness.\n\nThe most difficult benching decision involved **Victor Scott II** (47.23). While his elite sprint speed is a staple for our 5x5 Roto strategy, he was squeezed out by the depth of the current outfield and utility corps; his low projected batting position (#9) significantly hampered his daily efficiency score, making him a liability in a day packed with higher-order contributors. We are also closely monitoring the weather in Chicago, as **Carson Benge** (63.27) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.02) carry a 34% rain risk. Managers should stay alert for late-breaking news, as the volatility of lineup configurations\u2014specifically for **Dillon Dingler** and **Gary Sanchez** against tough arms like Garrett Crochet and Eury P\u00e9rez\u2014could see us pivot if actual batting orders deviate from our projections and further compress their already marginal scoring profiles.",
